--- Model 1e Key Results ---
Wells effect in FALL (reference):
  beta = -0.701, OR = 0.496, 95% CI [-1.168, -0.236], P(<0) = 0.9979

Wells effect in SPRING (fall + interaction):
  beta = -0.247, OR = 0.781, 95% CI [-1.307, 0.819], P(<0) = 0.6778

Interaction term (spring vs fall difference in Wells effect):
  beta = 0.454, 95% CI [-0.655, 1.540]
  P(interaction > 0) = 0.7901  [i.e. P(Wells effect smaller in spring)]

Predicted return probabilities (population-level):
  Group A Fall:   73.5% [65.7, 80.6]
  Group A Spring: 69.7% [53.8, 83.0]
  Group B Fall:   58.0% [47.3, 68.1]
  Group B Spring: 64.1% [41.6, 83.1]

Diagnostics: Rhat [1.000, 1.000], ESS [9818, 13156]

